Note that you have to cast the original value to an `Integer` after pulling it from the list.  The list has to be a list of `Object` since you want to be able to store multiple types of values in it.  Because of this, once you know you&#39;re dealing with an `Integer`, you then need to cast the value to `Integer` explicitly to have Java treat it as a numeric value.

