Maps have unique keys, so when you do

     for(int n : map.keySet()) {

you correctly consider each distinct element in the input.

When you do

    for(int n : nums) {

you no longer consider distinct elements. But that&#39;s wrong--the output is supposed to have only distinct elements. Your bucket `ArrayList`s should contain only unique integers that appear a certain number of times, not a list of every number that went into producing that count. When they contain non-distinct elements, the line

    for(int element : bucket[i]) {

generates incorrect output containing all elements from the input rather than distinct ones.

